DefaultReaderConfiguration.fullDescription: Collects events from Cisco Content Services Switches.

file.toolTipText: Directory or path to read from

string.toolTipText: Hostname of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

integer.toolTipText: Port number of the nDepth appliance to receive log data

select.toolTipText: Data routing (normalized alerts to Manager and/or raw data to nDepth)

integer.toolTipText: Number of seconds between log reads

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: Enterprise:Service Transition:\S+ -> \w+

FastPattern.description: 3, ServiceInfo: wcc, Computing slow start parameters
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ WCC-\d: Computing slow start parameters for newly activated service index \d+

FastPattern.description: 4, ServiceInfo: wcc, New service added to content rule
FastPattern.matcher: ^(\d+) ([-\w.]+) \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d\d:\d\d:\d\d (\d+)/(\d+) \d+ ([-A-Z]+)-(\d): (New service is added to content rule \d+)\. (Computing slow start value for service \d+)
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ WCC-\d: New service is added to content rule \d+\. Computing slow start value for service \d+

FastPattern.description: 5, ServiceInfo: wcc, Service default slow start count
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ WCC-\d: Service \d+ default slow start count is: \d+

FastPattern.description: 6, ServiceInfo: wcc, Service is out of slow start mode
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ WCC-\d: Service \d+ is out of slow start mode\.

FastPattern.description: 7, ServiceInfo: wcc, Service slow start count is computed
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ WCC-\d: Service \d+ slow start count is computed to: \d+

FastPattern.description: 8, ServiceInfo: wcc, State of service to be slow started
FastPattern.matcher: ^(\d+) ([-\w.]+) \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d\d:\d\d:\d\d (\d+)/(\d+) \d+ ([-A-Z]+)-(\d): State of service to be slow started is: ?(\d+) Live State is: ?(.+)
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ WCC-\d: State of service to be slow started is: ?\d+ Live State is:

FastField.defaultValue: State of service to be slow started is $6; Live State is $8
State of service to be slow started is $6; Live State is $8

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: SNMPAPI:SNMPAPI_Set:SET failure
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SYSSOFT-\d: SysLogSyncAgent sync timeout, time to sync clocks

FastPattern.description: 11, ServiceWarning: wcc, Resetting service slow start parameters
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ WCC-\d: Resetting service slow start parameters for service index \d+

FastPattern.description: 12, ServiceWarning: wcc, Service is not live
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ WCC-\d: Service \d+ is NOT live\.

FastPattern.description: 13, ServiceWarning: wcc, Service is still in slow start mode
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ WCC-\d: Service \d+ is still in slow start mode\.

FastPattern.description: 14, ServiceWarning: wcc, Slowstart parameters will not be computed
FastPattern.matcher: ^(\d+) ([-\w.]+) \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d\d:\d\d:\d\d (\d+)/(\d+) \d+ ([-A-Z]+)-(\d): (Service is not alive)\. (Slowstart parameters for service index \d+ will not be computed)\..*
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ WCC-\d: Service is not alive\. Slowstart parameters for service index \d+ will not be computed\.
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: Session logged out due to idle timer
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: TRAP:Authentication:Generated by: [\d.]+

FastField.defaultValue: Attempt to access CSS with an incorrect SNMP community string

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: Generic:SNMP Authentication > Failure from [\d.]+

FastField.defaultValue: Attempt to poll CSS using incorrect SNMP community string

FastPattern.matcher: ^(\d+) ([-\w.]+) \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d\d:\d\d:\d\d (\d+)/(\d+) \d+ ([-A-Z0-9]+)-(\d): RADIUS Authentication failed with reason code (\d+).*
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ RADIUS-\d: RADIUS Authentication failed with reason code \d+

^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ ACL-\d: (?:ACL match \d+:\d+ Discarding|\w+ SrcPort: \d+ DestPort: \d+|Source: [\d.]+|Dest: [\d.]+|ACL rule match \d+:\d+ Discarding packet, Log Enabled) *$

FastField.defaultValue: Incoming traffic matched an ACL statement: "$7"

FastFormatter.format: Incoming traffic matched on ACL statement "$9", $10

FastPattern.description: 22, ServiceInfo: circuit, status message for circuit
FastPattern.matcher: ^(\d+) ([-\w.]+) \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d\d:\d\d:\d\d (\d+)/(\d+) \d+ ([-A-Z]+)-(\d): (Circuit status message for circuit \d+ sent to CE [a-f\d]+) cause code is (\d+).*
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ CIRCUIT-\d: Circuit status message for circuit \d+ sent to CE [a-f\d]+ cause code is \d+

FastPattern.description: 23, ServiceInfo: flowmgr, allocation for a vector-loaded flow
FastPattern.matcher: ^(\d+) ([-\w.]+) \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d\d:\d\d:\d\d (\d+)/(\d+) \d+ ([-A-Z]+)-(\d): (Allocation for a vector-loaded flow), where the ?Flow = ([a-f\d]+).*
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ FLOWMGR-\d: Allocation for a vector-loaded flow
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ KAL-\d: kal_ServiceNotify: kalIndex = \d+ kalSvcEvent = \d+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: Generic:LINK (?:UP|DOWN) for \d+/\d+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ VLANMGR-\d: DeleteMacAddr\(\) called with VlanID = \d+ for MacAddr [-a-f\d:]{17}

FastField.defaultValue: Request to VLAN Manager to delete MAC address

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ WCC-\d: Route Change for IP Address \([\d.]+\)
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ CHMGR-\d: (?:Missing backup power supply|Cannot locate power supply: \d+)\.

FastPattern.description: 29, ServiceWarning: circut, circuit does not exist
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ CIRCUIT-\d: Error, Circuit \d+ does not exist\.
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ CIRCUIT-\d: Port \d+/\d+ is (?:down|up) for circuit \S+

FastPattern.description: 31, ServiceWarning: csdpeer, LR send list too small
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ CSDPEER-\d: LR Send list too small

FastField.defaultValue: Number of domain names sent by peer exceeded size of CSS list

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ FLOWMGR-\d: Flow manager received an illegal message with code \d+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ FLOWMGR-\d: FM_(?:ReTransTimeout: Re-Transmit timeout|Tcp: Handling generic FMTCP flow Re-Transmit) ERROR

FastPattern.description: 34, ServiceWarning: flowmgr, handling generic flow reject
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ FLOWMGR-\d: FM_UtilGenericTcpFlowReject: Handling Generic Flow REJECT

FastPattern.description: 35, ServiceWarning: flowmgr, exceeded outflow SYN count
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ FLOWMGR-\d: Exceeded outflow SYN count
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ FLOWMGR-\d: FM_GetIpv4Vc: Warning VCC_FP_IPV4_DC failed

FastPattern.description: 37, ServiceWarning: fp-drv, Could not allocate an MCID
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ FP[_-]DRV-\d: PrismImmFastPath::Send: Could not allocate an MCID. Remote message send aborted\.

FastPattern.description: 38, ServiceWarning: ipv4, IF config for circuit not found
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Ipv4IfMgrCctUpdateMsg: IF config for circuit \d+ not found

FastField.defaultValue: IF config for circuit not found

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Ipv4ReceivePacket: out of mbufs

FastPattern.description: 40, ServiceWarning: ipv4, unknown circuit in buffer
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Ipv4SfmArpTx: unknown circuit in buffer
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Ipv4SfmForwRx: bad IP version received

FastPattern.description: 42, ServiceWarning: ipv4, no VC for buffer
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Ipv4SfmForwTx: No VC for buffer

FastPattern.description: 43, ServiceWarning: ipv4, unknown logical port in buffer
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Ipv4SfmForwTx: unknown logical port in buffer
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Ipv4ApIoctl: unknown command:

FastPattern.description: 45, ServiceWarning: ipv4, vip redundancy callback on unregistered address
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: \(RIP\) VIP Redundancy callback on unregistered address

FastField.defaultValue: VIP redundancy callback on unregistered address

FastPattern.description: 46, ServiceWarning: ipv4, arp packet with unknown ingress port
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Ipv4SfmProcessArpFrame: ARP packet with unknown ingress port

FastField.defaultValue: ARP packet with unknown ingress port

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Ipv4SfmCmDeleteFlow: [\d.]+ response from VccRemoveVc
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Ipv4SfmProcessArpFrame: bad ARP packet received

FastPattern.description: 49, ServiceWarning: ipv4, bad ARP packet, mac types

FastField.defaultValue: Src Mac: 0x$8, Dst Mac: 0x$7, IP Type: $9

FastPattern.description: 50, ServiceWarning: ipv4, bad ARP packet, hw proto types
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: HW type: 0xdeadbeef Proto type: 0xdeadcafe *$

FastPattern.description: 51, ServiceWarning: ipv4, bad ARP packet, hlen plen
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: HLEN 0x[a-f\d]+ PLEN 0x[a-f\d]+ OPTPA-TSI-CSS1# 0x[a-f\d]+

FastPattern.description: 52, ServiceWarning: ipv4, bad ARP packet, sender target

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Duplicate IP address detected: [\d.]+ [-a-f\d:]{17}

FastPattern.description: 54, ServiceWarning: ipv4, duplicate IP address, incoming
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ IPV4-\d: Incoming CE 0x[a-f\d]+, incoming \(\d+ based\) SLP 0x[a-f\d]+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: Sshd:do_authenticated:ERROR->TSM Rejects connection
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: Enterprise:Service > Transition:nexthop\d+ -> down

FastField.defaultValue: Next hop IP address cannot be reached by CSS

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: clm_ProcessStdAction:ERROR->Action .+ not found
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: CLM:ERROR from clm_DispatchActionRoutine
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: SNMP:UNKNOWN RSP \(\d+\)

FastField.defaultValue: A valid SNMP agent is attempting to set an invalid object
A valid SNMP agent is attempting to set an invalid object

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: TSM:tsm_SendToCLA:ERROR->Write

FastField.defaultValue: Line data in stack after line was disconnected

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: ASUPPORT:as_SyncTask:ERROR->No registered reciever for MT:

FastPattern.description: 63, ServiceWarning: portmapper, no port mapping found
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ PORTMAPPER-\d: PortUnmap no Port mapping found\.

FastField.defaultValue: A source group is running out of portmappers

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ PUBLISH-\d: Unable to allocate tree memory
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ RADIUS-\d: (?:Return Auth Primary|Auth Primary|The id is \d+|RADIUS no memory available)

FastField.defaultValue: RADIUS server does not have correct attributes set up for the CSS

FastPattern.description: 66, ServiceWarning: sntp, sntp server has incorrect mode
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SNTP-\d: Sntp Server has incorrect mode \d+

FastPattern.description: 67, ServiceWarning: syssoft, connection already open or reserved
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SYSSOFT-\d: NP55[^:]+: Connection already open or reserved
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SYSSOFT-\d: VccAddVc:open conn failed w/ stat = [\d.]+; iVc \d+; eVc \d+
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SYSSOFT-\d: ONDM: Timeout downloading image to EPIF \d+ from the switch\.

FastPattern.description: 70, ServiceWarning: syssoft, could not download sub-module
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SYSSOFT-\d: ONDM: Could not download Sub-module \d+/\d+\.

FastPattern.description: 71, ServiceWarning: syssoft, could not open file
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SYSSOFT-\d: ONDM: Could not open file

FastPattern.description: 72, ServiceWarning: syssoft, no Sfm proxy for Slot
FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SYSSOFT-\d: ONDM:No Sfm proxy for Slot \d+\.
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SYSSOFT-\d: SYS:SysImmBind:Bind Collision TSM:
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SYSSOFT-\d: Invalid Target ?\(0x[a-f\d]+\) for Chassis Type, Message being dropped\.

FastField.defaultValue: Message sent to a non-existent slot and subslot in the chassis

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SYSSOFT-\d: Event not deliverable, msgq id = ?0x[a-f\d]+, event id = \d+, event name =

FastField.defaultValue: Event not deliverable because of full queue

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ SYSSOFT-\d: MPOOL:mpoolAutoAlloc:WARN->Overrun on MPOOL
^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ VPM-\d: VPM removed Vc deadbeef based on failure of port

FastField.defaultValue: VPM removed virtual circut based on failure of port

FastPattern.pattern: ^\d+ [-\w.]+ \d\d [A-Z]{3} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2} \d+/\d+ \d+ NETMAN-\d: Enterprise: Login Failure:vty\d [\d.]+ \S+
